title: About
text:
What are we doing?
This project is a collaboration between MDN and Global MedEd to verify and improve upon machine learning models that can help cardiologists more easily and reliably diagnose patients. We are particularly interested in the application of such models in low resource environments.
Specifically, we started by reproducing the results of the Echonet-Dynamic paper. This paper includes a machine-learning pipeline for estimating Ejection Fraction as well as a publicly available dataset of over ten thousand echocardiograms. This paper is focused on analysing only the left ventricle of the heart, but our team wishes to extend this to work with the right ventricle too. This is a challenge due to the absence of data available to us about the right ventricle, leading us to attempt a self-supervised approach (while learning along the way!).
See our progress updates for more details, and check out our links for our public Github repo!
